00:06:17.390 --> 00:06:20.690
Nintendo Existed at the Same Time as the Ottoman
Empire

00:06:20.690 --> 00:06:25.360
One is a modern Japanese entertainment company,
best known for a certain, red-suited, Italian

00:06:25.360 --> 00:06:26.360
plumber.

00:06:26.360 --> 00:06:31.200
The other was a vast Islamic empire founded
in the 14th century, that was ruled by sultans

00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:33.570
and once laid siege to Vienna in Austria.

00:06:33.570 --> 00:06:38.480
Both of these things existed at the same time
for thirty three whole years.

00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:42.450
The issue here is that Nintendo is way older
than you probably imagine, while the Ottoman

00:06:42.450 --> 00:06:45.970
Empire didn’t fall apart till much later
than you probably think.

00:06:45.970 --> 00:06:51.280
The Ottoman Empire only collapsed in 1922
as a result of losing WWI, after the Allies

00:06:51.280 --> 00:06:53.380
had carved up its territory for themselves.

00:06:53.380 --> 00:06:56.300
Nintendo, meanwhile, was founded way, way
back in 1889.

00:06:56.300 --> 00:07:01.530
At the time, Nintendo was a simple playing
card company, with nary an Italian plumber

00:07:01.530 --> 00:07:02.530
in sight.

00:07:02.530 --> 00:07:06.360
That’s probably not surprising, as Italy
had only been a unified state for less than

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:11.580
2 decades by that point, less than the time
separating us now from the release of Titanic.

00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:16.360
Europe was still (mostly) ruled by the Prussians,
Austro-Hungarians, Russians and Ottomans,

00:07:16.360 --> 00:07:19.560
and Britain had an empire that stretched all
the way around the world.

00:07:19.560 --> 00:07:24.290
Meanwhile, Japan had only just left two and
a half centuries of self-imposed isolation

00:07:24.290 --> 00:07:25.290
35 years beforehand.

