00:07:26.290 --> 00:07:30.880
The Ocean Contains 20 Million Tons of (unclaimed)
Gold

00:07:30.880 --> 00:07:35.190
Imagine if you discovered a near-limitless
supply of gold sitting right under your nose.

00:07:35.190 --> 00:07:36.820
All your worries would be over, right?

00:07:36.820 --> 00:07:39.720
Well, we’ve got some good news and some
bad news for you.

00:07:39.720 --> 00:07:44.630
The good is that such a stash of gold really
does exist, likely within easy driving distance.

00:07:44.630 --> 00:07:48.139
The bad is that its scattered over the entire
ocean.

00:07:48.139 --> 00:07:53.620
According to the National Oceanic and Atmospheric
Administration (NOAA), our planet’s oceans

00:07:53.620 --> 00:07:56.830
contain a staggering 20 million tons of unclaimed
gold.

00:07:56.830 --> 00:08:02.560
That’s enough to give every single person
alive today 9 pounds of the stuff… or to

00:08:02.560 --> 00:08:06.060
just hoard it for yourself and become the
richest person on the entire planet.

00:08:06.060 --> 00:08:08.200
The trouble, sadly, is getting at it.

00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:12.090
Much of the oceans’ gold is distributed
on a very, very fine level.

00:08:12.090 --> 00:08:16.610
As in, a single liter of seawater contains
13 billionths of a gram of gold.

00:08:16.610 --> 00:08:20.650
There’s just no way of extracting that,
and the stuff that’s concentrated is equally

00:08:20.650 --> 00:08:21.830
hard to get at.

00:08:21.830 --> 00:08:25.699
The biggest gold deposits are buried a mile
or two under the sea’s surface, and would

00:08:25.699 --> 00:08:28.740
require a massive mining operation to extract.

00:08:28.740 --> 00:08:31.060
Still, if you go looking, you might get lucky.

00:08:31.060 --> 00:08:36.559
In 2015, the nation of Colombia discovered
$1 billion worth of sunken Spanish gold sitting

00:08:36.559 --> 00:08:38.909
right off the coast of Cartagena.

