00:08:39.909 --> 00:08:44.290
The Biggest Quake in History Hit 23 on the
Richter Scale

00:08:44.290 --> 00:08:48.120
If you live in earthquake country, you’ll
know anything above about a 4 on the Richter

00:08:48.120 --> 00:08:49.829
Scale is terrifying.

00:08:49.829 --> 00:08:53.199
The 2010 earthquake that leveled Haiti was
a magnitude 7.0.

00:08:53.199 --> 00:08:57.920
The 1964 earthquake that nearly upended the
whole of Alaska was 9.2.

00:08:57.920 --> 00:09:03.410
The largest in modern history was a 9.6 off
the coast of Chile, and that caused 35 foot

00:09:03.410 --> 00:09:07.130
waves 6,200 miles from the epicenter.

00:09:07.130 --> 00:09:10.160
But there’s actually an even-bigger earthquake
on record.

00:09:10.160 --> 00:09:15.449
It went beyond standard measurements and hit
a devastating 23 on the Richter Scale.

00:09:15.449 --> 00:09:19.129
That estimate comes courtesy of NASA, who
observed the quake in action.

00:09:19.129 --> 00:09:23.059
That’s right, thankfully for all life on
Earth, the quake happened millions of lightyears

00:09:23.059 --> 00:09:24.600
away, at a star known as SGR J1550-5418.

00:09:24.600 --> 00:09:33.920
The ‘starquake’ was big enough to destroy
everything in a 10 light year radius.

00:09:33.920 --> 00:09:37.860
Starquakes are caused when the crust of a
magnetar – a super, super dense neutron

00:09:37.860 --> 00:09:42.279
star that packs the mass of more than million
Earths into an area the size of Manhattan

00:09:42.279 --> 00:09:43.290
– cracks.

00:09:43.290 --> 00:09:46.560
The resulting release of energy is one of
the deadliest events in the universe.

00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:49.619
Any nearby planets would be wiped out instantly.

00:09:49.619 --> 00:09:55.800
One single, 20 minute quake releases more
energy than our sun does in 20 whole years.

00:09:55.800 --> 00:09:58.940
Thank God we haven’t got any in our galactic
neighborhood.

