00:11:02.970 --> 00:11:05.889
You Make History Every Time You Shuffle a
Deck of Cards

00:11:05.889 --> 00:11:08.980
Stop reading this for a second, and go find
yourself a deck of cards.

00:11:08.980 --> 00:11:09.980
Got it?

00:11:09.980 --> 00:11:14.430
Right, now give that mother a shuffle and
lay the cards in the order they come out.

00:11:14.430 --> 00:11:19.100
Congratulations, you’ve just done something
completely unique in the whole of human history.

00:11:19.100 --> 00:11:24.519
52 cards may not sound like much, but it creates
an insane number of possible combinations.

00:11:24.519 --> 00:11:30.440
Highbrow British quiz show QI calculated the
number at 52 factorial, which means 52 times

00:11:30.440 --> 00:11:33.260
51, times 50, times 49… etc.

00:11:33.260 --> 00:11:34.959
Written out, it looks like this:

00:11:34.959 --> 00:11:35.959
80,658,175,170,943,878,571,660,636,856,403,766,975,289,505,440,883,277,824,000,000,000,000.

00:11:35.959 --> 00:11:40.930
That’s a big number, but we’re not even
close to describing just how insanely big.

00:11:40.930 --> 00:11:46.230
The QI ‘Elves’ phrased it like this: “If
every star in our galaxy had a trillion planets,

00:11:46.230 --> 00:11:50.350
each with a trillion people living on them,
and each of these people has a trillion packs

00:11:50.350 --> 00:11:55.510
of cards and somehow they manage to make unique
shuffles 1,000 times per second, and they’d

00:11:55.510 --> 00:12:01.050
been doing that since the Big Bang, they’d
only just now be starting to repeat shuffles.”

00:12:01.050 --> 00:12:02.050
So there you have it.

00:12:02.050 --> 00:12:06.009
If you wanna make history, don’t cure cancer
or invent a new device or conquer half the

00:12:06.009 --> 00:12:07.009
world.

00:12:07.009 --> 00:12:09.089
Just grab a pack of cards and get shuffling.

00:12:09.089 --> 00:12:28.589
We guarantee the results will be historically
unique.

